    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-01T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-01T23:00:00-05:00" n="743"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">846G.2393/6–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-02T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 2, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 3—2:35 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 519. Central Bank requesting Embassy office explore possibility US
                    military airlift to Hong Kong at “nominal” cost 5 million silver dollars being
                    minted at Philadelphia for Chinese Government. Airlift to be completed
                    mid-June.</p>
                <p>Central Bank claims commercial airlift costs prohibitive and delivery urgent for
                    purpose expedite introduction new currency program.</p>
                <p>Would appreciate instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
